body:
I wanted to have a nice game of League before I go to work, I just got through Champion Select and then suddenly when I was about to go into the loading screen before entering the game... it crashes. I hit the "reconnect" button, but I was still unable to reconnect! I hit it and hit it, but to no avail. I sent several bug reports -- trouble-shooted the game, exited out of I-tunes, updated my laptop, etc. But it was to no avail! I couldn't reconnect! The game ended and I was only able to connect to the stats screen where you go at the end of every game. I apologized but only the players of the enemy team were there. I then thought -- to my idiocy -- "It might have been a bad server.." so with a bit of hope -- I tried to get into another game -- but it happened again. after only a moment, I get Leaver Buster. I was in the new client.... I tried get into the old client but got nothing. my game was also saying that I wasn't connected to the internet..... obviously it was wrong because I'm currently typing this just after it had happened!

In the games that I was supposed to connect to I was supposed to be in these roles:

Top Lane - {{champion:17}} (omega squad skin) {{summoner:14}} {{summoner:4}} 

Jungle - {{champion:78}} (Star Guardian skin) {{summoner:11}}  {{summoner:4}} 

for those of you who were in these games that I was supposed to be in -- I'M SO SORRY! I hope you all understand.

I won't be playing until this is fixed -- I'm gonna give it about.... 24 hours, if not then 2 days max. Depending. I tried everything I knew. heck I have Razor Cortex game booster to help with lag problems! Nothing has worked. Riot, please fix this, and get your 'Leaver Buster bot' to know the difference between a crash and hitting the 'leave game' button.
